1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:03,070
♪

2
00:00:03,103 --> 00:00:05,739
Narrator: 30 minutes
after the extermination team

3
00:00:05,772 --> 00:00:07,440
launched their offensive,

4
00:00:07,474 --> 00:00:11,511
even as the fierce battle
unfolded inside,

5
00:00:11,545 --> 00:00:13,247
an immense number of citizens

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:15,816
who had been hypnotized
by pouf’s wing scales

7
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:18,819
were still lined up
beyond the walls

8
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:21,221
waiting patiently
for the sorting process

9
00:00:21,255 --> 00:00:24,492
that would turn them
into soldier ants.

10
00:00:26,293 --> 00:00:29,496
Meanwhile, a creature
much like the ones

11
00:00:29,530 --> 00:00:32,633
they would soon become
began to stir.

12
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,486
( Door creaking )

13
00:00:56,123 --> 00:00:57,091
♪

14
00:00:57,124 --> 00:00:59,059
( Singing in Japanese )

15
00:01:41,502 --> 00:01:43,437
( Electricity crackling )

16
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,759
Killua: Okay,
i’m all charged up.

17
00:02:25,078 --> 00:02:26,379
♪

18
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:34,020
( Nen whooshing )

19
00:02:37,457 --> 00:02:40,360
Someone’s watching me, and...

20
00:02:42,696 --> 00:02:44,765
I think it’s someone I know.

21
00:03:25,172 --> 00:03:27,274
No one’s there?

22
00:03:27,307 --> 00:03:28,341
( Gasps )

23
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,310
( Footsteps pattering )

24
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:10,117
Narrator: Her appearance
hadn’t totally changed,

25
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:13,320
but clearly palm
was no longer the same person,

26
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:17,290
and that rattled
killua’s nerves.

27
00:04:21,762 --> 00:04:26,333
Killua: She’s been captured
by the royal guard

28
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:29,269
and transformed.

29
00:04:30,571 --> 00:04:33,507
If gon sees
what’s happened to palm,

30
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,276
he’s not gonna be able
to handle it.

31
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:40,080
There’s no room left
inside of his heart,

32
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:43,416
not for something
as awful as this.

33
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:46,286
I don’t know how far
the transformation’s gone,

34
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,422
but if her psyche’s
been altered, too...

35
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,594
Gon could totally lose it.

36
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:02,636
I have to find out
right here and now.

37
00:05:07,574 --> 00:05:11,445
We still have a chance.
Palm approached me herself.

38
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:13,547
♪

39
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,048
Hey, palm?

40
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,351
( Thinking ) Palm must
have sensed my presence

41
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:20,387
before I was able
to sense hers,

42
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,455
and if that’s the case...

43
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,593
She used that power
she told us about.

44
00:05:26,627 --> 00:05:28,329
( Palm chuckles )

45
00:05:28,362 --> 00:05:32,333
Once I used my ability,
it was really quite simple.

46
00:05:34,168 --> 00:05:35,436
Killua: I thought she could use

47
00:05:35,469 --> 00:05:38,138
some kind of divination
to locate people,

48
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:41,075
but it’s probably
closer to clairvoyance.

49
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,645
From her position,

50
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:47,447
palm shouldn’t have
been able to see me.

51
00:05:47,481 --> 00:05:50,584
That can only mean
she must have been watching me

52
00:05:50,617 --> 00:05:52,285
by some other method.

53
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:56,656
And if palm had changed sides,

54
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,392
she definitely
would have backed off.

55
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:02,496
Clairvoyance is most effective
from a distance,

56
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:04,464
and if she is an enemy,

57
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,133
she shouldn’t
remember me anymore.

58
00:06:07,501 --> 00:06:12,339
She approached me,
so she must remember me...

59
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,642
Remember us.

60
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:20,147
Palm: You are...

61
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,115
Killua, right?

62
00:06:22,149 --> 00:06:24,451
( Killua gasps )

63
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:26,052
I knew it.

64
00:06:28,155 --> 00:06:30,057
She does remember!

65
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:35,562
Palm: Where’s gon? ( Sighs )

66
00:06:35,596 --> 00:06:37,798
Once he sees what I have become,

67
00:06:37,831 --> 00:06:41,134
do you think
that he’s going to hate me?

68
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:42,703
( Killua sighs )

69
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:45,639
Gon doesn’t judge people
by their appearances.

70
00:06:45,672 --> 00:06:51,044
Also, you’re assuming
he liked you in the first place.

71
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:54,048
Palm: You always act like
such a spiteful little brat,

72
00:06:54,081 --> 00:06:55,082
now, don’t you?

73
00:06:56,216 --> 00:06:58,452
Well, no matter.

74
00:06:58,485 --> 00:07:01,355
I have nothing to gain
from your pity.

75
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:05,259
In fact, it wouldn’t
be helpful to anyone at all.

76
00:07:05,292 --> 00:07:07,394
So tell me where gon is.

77
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:10,096
Killua: Gon is with pitou
at the moment.

78
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:11,298
I’m sure he’s--

79
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:13,266
♪

80
00:07:16,303 --> 00:07:21,241
Why can she see me,
but she can’t see gon?

81
00:07:25,245 --> 00:07:26,713
Palm: Is something wrong?

82
00:07:26,747 --> 00:07:29,483
( Killua gasps )

83
00:07:29,516 --> 00:07:32,319
So was it just by chance
you found me?

84
00:07:32,352 --> 00:07:35,589
Palm: Huh?
What are you talking about?

85
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:39,126
You were the one who just walked
around the corner and found me.

86
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,528
Killua: You’re wrong.
I sensed you.

87
00:07:41,562 --> 00:07:43,264
I felt you watching me,

88
00:07:43,297 --> 00:07:45,766
and that’s the reason
I came this way...

89
00:07:47,201 --> 00:07:49,570
But i’m sure
you noticed me first.

90
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:53,440
Why are you lying?

91
00:07:56,577 --> 00:07:58,746
Palm: You are
such a little pest.

92
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:01,048
Where is gon?

93
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:03,717
Killua: Answer me first,
and maybe i’ll tell you.

94
00:08:05,686 --> 00:08:09,557
Is it possible that I only
noticed palm watching me

95
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:12,093
when she actually
laid eyes on me?

96
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,728
Does that mean
she saw me once, then left

97
00:08:14,761 --> 00:08:17,497
before I had the chance
to sense her presence?

98
00:08:17,531 --> 00:08:20,567
Then she used clairvoyance
to watch me follow her

99
00:08:20,601 --> 00:08:22,136
and turned around

100
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:25,039
so it’d look like she was
coming my direction?

101
00:08:28,742 --> 00:08:31,111
Palm: One last time.

102
00:08:32,813 --> 00:08:34,748
Where can I find gon?

103
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:41,422
Killua: I’m not telling you.

104
00:08:41,455 --> 00:08:44,224
You’re an enemy, aren’t you?

105
00:08:44,258 --> 00:08:46,260
( Palm groans )

106
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:49,163
♪

107
00:08:57,271 --> 00:08:58,572
( Killua gasps )

108
00:09:00,574 --> 00:09:04,078
Palm: It seems
i’ve made a mistake.

109
00:09:05,379 --> 00:09:08,983
There are better ways
to use my abilities.

110
00:09:09,016 --> 00:09:11,318
Instead of
bottling up my rage...

111
00:09:13,754 --> 00:09:17,424
It would have been better
to yield to it completely!

112
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:30,103
Killua: Damn. She’s dangerous.

113
00:09:30,137 --> 00:09:32,573
Palm: Better to let
everything out,

114
00:09:32,606 --> 00:09:34,241
don’t you think?

115
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:38,311
A perfect example
of that would be

116
00:09:38,345 --> 00:09:41,315
my desire to kill you!

117
00:09:41,348 --> 00:09:44,251
♪

118
00:09:52,359 --> 00:09:53,660
Killua: Huh?

119
00:09:56,563 --> 00:10:00,033
( Palm laughs )

120
00:10:01,368 --> 00:10:04,671
Well? What are you gonna do now?

121
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:09,810
Will you stay silent?

122
00:10:09,843 --> 00:10:12,145
Give up and talk?

123
00:10:21,388 --> 00:10:23,323
( Heels clattering )

124
00:10:28,896 --> 00:10:30,698
Or will you just die?

125
00:10:30,731 --> 00:10:32,733
Which is it?

126
00:10:37,237 --> 00:10:38,605
( Palm laughing )

127
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:40,574
( Blows striking )

128
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:52,819
Narrator:
Palm’s ability, black widow,

129
00:10:52,853 --> 00:10:54,822
turns her hair into a weapon

130
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:58,158
that changes shape
according to her emotions.

131
00:10:58,192 --> 00:11:02,563
Although powerful, its function
is entirely defensive.

132
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:07,133
However, what made
black widow frightening

133
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:08,902
was that it allowed her

134
00:11:08,936 --> 00:11:11,705
to rely on her armor of hair
for protection

135
00:11:11,738 --> 00:11:17,077
while at the same time focusing
all of her energy on offense.

136
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:24,818
( Killua groans )

137
00:11:29,156 --> 00:11:31,759
Gon: Whoa! Hey!
Miss palm, please,

138
00:11:31,792 --> 00:11:33,661
you’ve gotta stop
using your hatsu!

139
00:11:35,629 --> 00:11:38,031
Killua: Palm is
originally an enhancer.

140
00:11:38,065 --> 00:11:39,934
The difference it makes
when your ability

141
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:42,136
is a perfect match
is incredible.

142
00:11:42,169 --> 00:11:45,572
I blocked the attack,
but I still took damage.

143
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:51,244
If the fight drags on,
i’m totally done for,

144
00:11:51,278 --> 00:11:55,249
but even so, I can’t run away.

145
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:59,119
I can tell that gon’s mind
is already at its limit.

146
00:11:59,152 --> 00:12:01,254
And while he sits there
waiting for pitou,

147
00:12:01,288 --> 00:12:03,223
he’s barely
holding himself together.

148
00:12:06,827 --> 00:12:08,729
( Palm squeals )

149
00:12:11,698 --> 00:12:13,200
Killua: I can’t let them meet.

150
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:17,537
There still might be a shred
of palm’s heart in there...

151
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:18,839
And if there is...

152
00:12:20,941 --> 00:12:22,943
It’s not gonna help.

153
00:12:39,893 --> 00:12:41,595
Palm!

154
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:44,197
Why the hell are you
looking for gon?

155
00:12:44,231 --> 00:12:48,168
If you have a good reason,
i’ll tell you where he is!

156
00:12:48,202 --> 00:12:51,772
Palm: Huh?
Why are you asking now?

157
00:12:51,805 --> 00:12:55,108
There’s no reason, actually.
I just want to see him.

158
00:12:55,142 --> 00:12:57,811
He’s probably nearby.

159
00:12:57,845 --> 00:12:59,914
Don’t worry.
I’ll find him myself.

160
00:12:59,947 --> 00:13:02,917
Just as soon as i’ve
killed you, that is!

161
00:13:10,257 --> 00:13:11,525
Killua: Sorry!

162
00:13:14,228 --> 00:13:17,965
I panicked earlier,
and I called you the enemy.

163
00:13:17,998 --> 00:13:19,199
You might look different,

164
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:20,901
but you’re still palm,
aren’t you?

165
00:13:20,934 --> 00:13:22,302
( Palm gasps )

166
00:13:22,336 --> 00:13:24,805
Killua: Gon is
suffering right now.

167
00:13:24,838 --> 00:13:28,308
Someone he deeply respects
was ruthlessly altered.

168
00:13:28,342 --> 00:13:30,911
That person
had his soul taken away,

169
00:13:30,944 --> 00:13:33,280
and right now,
gon is facing off

170
00:13:33,313 --> 00:13:35,315
against the person
who’s responsible.

171
00:13:35,349 --> 00:13:37,785
If he sees you now,

172
00:13:37,818 --> 00:13:40,654
looking so different
than you did before...

173
00:13:44,658 --> 00:13:46,760
( Gasps )

174
00:13:46,793 --> 00:13:50,263
Gon is gonna totally snap.

175
00:13:57,271 --> 00:14:00,241
So when you see him...

176
00:14:00,274 --> 00:14:04,211
Make sure
you call him by his name first.

177
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,916
Say, "gon."

178
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:17,157
That’s it. That’s my condition.

179
00:14:20,227 --> 00:14:22,763
Let him know you’re okay.

180
00:14:28,969 --> 00:14:31,138
Before we entered the palace,

181
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:33,774
gon was really worried
about you.

182
00:14:33,807 --> 00:14:35,842
He told me that himself.

183
00:14:40,247 --> 00:14:43,984
So, please,
give him some peace of mind.

184
00:14:44,017 --> 00:14:45,952
♪

185
00:14:47,921 --> 00:14:50,023
Narrator: He was
just buying time.

186
00:14:50,057 --> 00:14:52,326
He had no intention
of letting them meet,

187
00:14:52,359 --> 00:14:55,229
at least, not at first.

188
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:59,065
( Killua crying )

189
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:03,870
Please, if you can...

190
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:06,774
Put his mind at ease.

191
00:15:08,775 --> 00:15:11,544
Please, only you...

192
00:15:11,578 --> 00:15:13,580
Can do that now, palm.

193
00:15:18,118 --> 00:15:19,953
No one else...

194
00:15:19,987 --> 00:15:22,756
Can reach him.

195
00:15:22,789 --> 00:15:25,091
It’s all up to you now.

196
00:15:29,763 --> 00:15:32,032
I just...

197
00:15:34,034 --> 00:15:37,170
I can’t help him anymore!

198
00:15:37,204 --> 00:15:39,139
( Wailing )

199
00:15:47,014 --> 00:15:50,651
Narrator: As soon as those words
had escaped killua’s lips,

200
00:15:50,684 --> 00:15:54,254
the dam within him
suddenly burst.

201
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:56,223
( Killua wailing )

202
00:16:07,201 --> 00:16:08,536
( Shaiapouf gasps )

203
00:16:08,569 --> 00:16:10,271
Look. He’s defenseless.

204
00:16:10,304 --> 00:16:14,475
So new strategy,
kill him now, number one.

205
00:16:14,508 --> 00:16:16,443
♪

206
00:16:21,448 --> 00:16:24,618
Narrator: Earlier, when palm
had infiltrated the palace

207
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:26,286
and made her way to the exit

208
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:29,056
knov had placed
near the stairway, pitou’s en,

209
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:32,225
which had been lying dormant,
suddenly switched on.

210
00:16:32,259 --> 00:16:36,063
Surrounded
by the brutally evil aura,

211
00:16:36,096 --> 00:16:39,366
she felt as though she
would soon be crushed to dust,

212
00:16:39,399 --> 00:16:40,700
and, in an instant,

213
00:16:40,734 --> 00:16:45,105
came to the very same
conclusion that knov had.

214
00:16:45,138 --> 00:16:51,077
Then as she watched pouf slowly
and silently descend the stairs,

215
00:16:51,111 --> 00:16:52,512
she made her decision.

216
00:16:52,546 --> 00:16:53,547
( Thump )

217
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,816
She tried to take her own life

218
00:16:55,849 --> 00:17:00,520
so as to look like a victim who
could not bear bizeff’s abuse,

219
00:17:00,554 --> 00:17:04,391
but pitou prevented that
from happening.

220
00:17:05,726 --> 00:17:08,762
As one cannot help
but shiver in the cold,

221
00:17:08,795 --> 00:17:12,465
no one could blame palm for
reflexively using her own aura

222
00:17:12,499 --> 00:17:14,601
to protect herself
from pitou’s,

223
00:17:14,635 --> 00:17:18,472
which she did the moment
she felt exposed to it.

224
00:17:18,505 --> 00:17:22,042
The royal guard
was interested in her aura,

225
00:17:22,075 --> 00:17:24,444
and, after receiving
approval from the king,

226
00:17:24,478 --> 00:17:26,480
who agreed to forego a meal,

227
00:17:26,513 --> 00:17:31,084
pitou and pouf made her
experimental soldier number one.

228
00:17:31,118 --> 00:17:33,687
Those who remembered their pasts

229
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:37,490
had shown stronger mental
fortitude than the others.

230
00:17:37,524 --> 00:17:40,560
This phenomenon
was most noticeable

231
00:17:40,594 --> 00:17:42,463
in ants who possessed
nen abilities.

232
00:17:42,496 --> 00:17:45,499
It was becoming clear
that memories of the past

233
00:17:45,532 --> 00:17:50,504
had a tendency to both assist
and deter the soldiers’ growth.

234
00:17:50,537 --> 00:17:53,573
Instances that caused
the most interference

235
00:17:53,607 --> 00:17:58,112
were generally tied to memories
leading to emotional reactions.

236
00:17:58,145 --> 00:18:01,115
Knowing this,
the two royal guards concluded

237
00:18:01,148 --> 00:18:03,183
that they should use
pitou’s Dr. Blythe

238
00:18:03,217 --> 00:18:04,518
to destroy the connection

239
00:18:04,551 --> 00:18:08,055
between palm’s memories
and her emotions.

240
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:11,124
The experiments
on cheetu and leol

241
00:18:11,158 --> 00:18:14,228
confirmed that those who
retained more of their memories

242
00:18:14,261 --> 00:18:18,298
emerged from their cocoons much
sooner than their counterparts.

243
00:18:19,466 --> 00:18:21,368
To quickly conquer humanity,

244
00:18:21,401 --> 00:18:22,769
the best course of action

245
00:18:22,803 --> 00:18:25,139
would be to leave soldiers
with their memories

246
00:18:25,172 --> 00:18:27,307
while maintaining
strict control over them.

247
00:18:29,042 --> 00:18:33,580
As it happened, palm was
the perfect Guinea pig.

248
00:18:35,082 --> 00:18:37,217
The success of the experiment

249
00:18:37,251 --> 00:18:40,387
would signify
the end of the human race.

250
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:42,722
Shaiapouf: Okay,
now get going, number one!

251
00:18:42,756 --> 00:18:45,726
Beat that kid to death,
and make it painful!

252
00:18:45,759 --> 00:18:46,727
Palm: Shut up.

253
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:47,728
Shaiapouf: What?

254
00:18:47,761 --> 00:18:50,464
( Killua gasps )

255
00:18:52,599 --> 00:18:55,268
Palm: My name is palm,

256
00:18:55,302 --> 00:18:57,738
palm Siberia.

257
00:18:57,771 --> 00:18:59,673
( Shaiapouf gasps )

258
00:19:01,441 --> 00:19:03,476
Palm: Don’t call me
"number one"!

259
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,445
♪

260
00:19:12,052 --> 00:19:14,421
I will never...

261
00:19:14,454 --> 00:19:16,623
Become a tool for ants...

262
00:19:18,225 --> 00:19:21,228
Not even if it kills me.

263
00:19:35,742 --> 00:19:37,277
( Killua gasps )

264
00:19:42,082 --> 00:19:44,318
Palm: Thank you, killua.

265
00:19:44,351 --> 00:19:46,687
I owe it all to you.

266
00:19:48,355 --> 00:19:52,059
It’s like there was
a wall inside my head.

267
00:19:52,092 --> 00:19:55,128
My emotions
were separate from my body,

268
00:19:55,162 --> 00:19:58,132
and there was
nothing I could do.

269
00:19:58,165 --> 00:20:02,136
It was like that
ever since I woke up.

270
00:20:02,169 --> 00:20:06,140
But then someone
removed that wall.

271
00:20:06,173 --> 00:20:08,342
It was you, killua.

272
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:10,711
Don’t ever think
that you’re powerless.

273
00:20:10,744 --> 00:20:13,547
( Killua gasps )

274
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:16,550
Palm: If it means helping gon,

275
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:19,753
i’m ready to do
anything in my power.

276
00:20:21,121 --> 00:20:23,757
But please don’t forget,

277
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:27,627
out of all the people
gon needs in his life,

278
00:20:27,661 --> 00:20:30,264
he needs you the most.

279
00:20:30,297 --> 00:20:32,366
( Killua gasping )

280
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,614
( Shaiapouf groans )

281
00:20:47,648 --> 00:20:48,682
Menthuthuyoupi: What is it?

282
00:20:48,715 --> 00:20:50,817
Shaiapouf: Total failure,

283
00:20:50,851 --> 00:20:52,820
and that’s all there is to it.

284
00:20:52,853 --> 00:20:53,821
Menthuthuyoupi: Huh?

285
00:20:55,355 --> 00:20:57,557
Shaiapouf:
Slow and steady wins the race.

286
00:20:57,591 --> 00:20:59,860
Seems soldiers have
no need of memories

287
00:20:59,893 --> 00:21:02,028
or senseless emotions,

288
00:21:02,062 --> 00:21:07,034
which also means I am no longer
in need of pitou’s power.

289
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:12,439
If it’s soldiers I require,
I can create them on my own.

290
00:21:12,472 --> 00:21:14,474
♪

291
00:21:14,508 --> 00:21:18,145
In fact, that will make it
that much easier

292
00:21:18,178 --> 00:21:23,750
to build a new kingdom
fit for the king and myself.

293
00:21:25,319 --> 00:21:27,254
( Singing in Japanese )

